        "text": "<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the difficulties facing non-native speakers of English is its intonation pattern. English is a content language, which means that the more meaningful words in a sentence are emphasized while the less meaning words are not.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">This pattern of intonation and stress may contrast with a non-native speaker’s natural pattern of speech and needs to be a practiced. The following link provides a thorough discussion of the topic.</span></p><h4><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Click on the link below. Listen to the video. Then answer the questions.</strong></h4><p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oWP9Riq-ZBg\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oWP9Riq-ZBg</a></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Now answer the questions about phrases introducing yourself:</span></p><h4><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">1. The speaker mentions 4 sentences you can use to give your name. List the two complete sentences and the short (contracted) forms of these:</span></h4><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">a) Full sentence: </span>*I am/My name is*<span style=\"color: rgb(83, 129, 53);\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">(NAME)&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">b) Sentence with contraction: </span>*I'm/My name's*<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (NAME)</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">c) Full sentence: </span>*My name is/I am*<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (NAME)</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">d) Sentence with contraction: </span>*My name's/I'm*<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (NAME)</span></p><h4><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">2. What word does the speaker say you should use to make saying your name more fluently? </span>*I'm*</h4><h4><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">3. What word can you use to say your hometown or your work?</span></h4><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">I'm </span>*from*<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (place). I'm </span>*from*<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (work).</span></p><h4><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">4. What three sentences do you say in response to the sentence “Nice to meet you.”?</span></h4><p>*Nice to meet you./Nice to meet you, too./Good to meet you./Nice to meet you/Nice to meet you, too/Good to meet you*</p><p>*Nice to meet you./Nice to meet you, too./Good to meet you./Nice to meet you/Nice to meet you, too/Good to meet you*</p><p>*Nice to meet you./Nice to meet you, too./Good to meet you./Nice to meet you/Nice to meet you, too/Good to meet you*</p>"
